To me, it is not a vowel, but a dipthong - 2 vowels conjoined by a short, smooth transition:
knee-er (sort of like it's spelled)...

On 10. Nov.,`07, at 03:22 EST, Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com wrote:

many people don't clearly use 
either Eat or It in the NEAR set, 
but a vowel somewhere between.
